## GitHub Actions CI/CD

### Required Secrets

Go to **GitHub repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions** and add:

| Secret Name           | Value                        |
|-----------------------|------------------------------|
| EC2_IP                | Your EC2 public IP           |
| EC2_USER              | ubuntu                       |
| EC2_SSH_KEY           | Full content of your .pem file |
| AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID     | Your AWS access key          |
| AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY | Your AWS secret key          |
| AWS_REGION            | Your AWS region (e.g. us-east-1) |
| SG_ID                 | Your security group ID       |

---

### Main Workflow — deploy.yml

Triggers on every push to master branch.

```yaml
name: Deploy to EC2

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - master

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Get GitHub IP and Open Firewall
        run: |
          GITHUB_IP=$(curl -s https://api.ipify.org)
          echo "GITHUB_IP=$GITHUB_IP" >> $GITHUB_ENV
          echo "Opening firewall for $GITHUB_IP"
          aws ec2 authorize-security-group-ingress \
            --group-id "${{ secrets.SG_ID }}" \
            --protocol tcp \
            --port 22 \
            --cidr ${GITHUB_IP}/32 || true
        env:
          AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}
          AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY: ${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}
          AWS_DEFAULT_REGION: ${{ secrets.AWS_REGION }}

      - name: Deploy to EC2
        uses: appleboy/ssh-action@master
        with:
          host: ${{ secrets.EC2_IP }}
          username: ${{ secrets.EC2_USER }}
          key: ${{ secrets.EC2_SSH_KEY }}
          script: |
            export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm"
            [ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ] && \. "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh"
            export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/bin
            cd /home/ubuntu/testing-purose
            git fetch origin
            git reset --hard origin/master
            sudo chown -R ubuntu:ubuntu /home/ubuntu/testing-purose
            pm2 stop app || true
            pm2 start /home/ubuntu/testing-purose/backend/app.js --name app
            pm2 save
            sudo systemctl restart nginx
            echo "Deployed successfully!"

      - name: Remove IP from Firewall
        if: always()
        run: |
          echo "Closing firewall for $GITHUB_IP"
          aws ec2 revoke-security-group-ingress \
            --group-id "${{ secrets.SG_ID }}" \
            --protocol tcp \
            --port 22 \
            --cidr ${GITHUB_IP}/32 || true
        env:
          AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}
          AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY: ${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}
          AWS_DEFAULT_REGION: ${{ secrets.AWS_REGION }}
```

