## QA Branch Setup

### Create QA Branch

On GitHub, create a new branch called `qa` from master.

### Clone QA branch on EC2

```bash
cd /home/ubuntu
git clone -b qa https://github.com/Madhan1417/testing-purose.git testing-purose-qa
```

### Update Nginx for QA

```bash
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default
```

Add QA paths:

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;

    # Production Frontend
    location / {
        root /home/ubuntu/testing-purose/frontend;
        index index.html;
    }

    # Production Backend
    location /backend/ {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:3000/;
    }

    # QA Frontend
    location /qa/ {
        root /home/ubuntu/testing-purose-qa/frontend;
        index index.html;
    }

    # QA Backend
    location /qa-backend/ {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:3001/;
    }
}
```

### Start QA Backend

```bash
pm2 start /home/ubuntu/testing-purose-qa/backend/app.js --name qa-app -- --port 3001
pm2 save
```

